Olalekan Adetayo, Abuja The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), on Monday, sent condolences to the government and people of Delta State on the death of a former Federal Commissioner for Works, Major General Orho Obada (retd.). Obada, Aide-de-Camp to Nigeria’s first President, Dr Nnamdi Azikwe, reportedly died at a private hospital In Warri, Delta State, after a brief illness on Sunday. Aged 81, Obada also served as the commissioner representing Delta State in the Federal Revenue Mobilisation Allocation and Fiscal Commission in 2006. In a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, the President commiserated with Agbarho Kingdom in Ughelli North Local Council and Urhobo Progress Union. He urged the deceased’s associates to draw strength from the legacies that he left behind, most commendably his willingness to serve the country, and humanity. “President Buhari notes, with sadness, that the former acting Chief of Air Staff served in many strategic positions in the military, and his wealth of experience had been helpful to the country for many years after his retirement. “The President prays that the almighty God will accept the soul of the departed, and comfort his family,” the statement read. 